==Rogue==
Rogue is a Scheme-to-x64 compiler written (almost) entirely in Scheme by me and a friend for my compilation class. It uses a limited, but usable, subset of Scheme. It is indeed usable enough that Rogue can compile itself. Only once though, because it lacks a fully-functionnal <code>eval</code> function and because it would take a formidable amout of time, Rogue having little to no optimizations.

It was written and "bootstrapped" using [http://dynamo.iro.umontreal.ca/wiki/index.php/Main_Page Gambit Scheme].
